    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">328 Mickle Street</name> 
                   <date when="1887-05-03"><name type="place">Camden New Jersey</name><ptr target="uva.00551_n1"/>
                    May 3, '87</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p>Your letter rec'd &#38; welcomed as always&#8212;My visit to N Y was a hasty flash only&#8212;I am
                more &#38; more wretchedly physically disabled, &#38; feel better off here in my own
                den&#8212;the "Anne Gilchrist" book<ptr target="n3900"/> is a wonderfully well done Vol. &#38; interesting very to
                me because I knew &#38; loved Mrs. G&#8212;but I doubt whether it contains much (or any
                thing) for you&#8212;I can loan you my copy if you wish&#8212;I will certainly keep you posted
                ab't myself, or any literary movement or change or happening of my work&#8212;</p>
            <closer>
                <signed>Walt Whitman</signed>
            </closer>
        </body>
    </text>
